From: admin@{{ domain }}
To: contact@{{ domain }}
Subject: Credentials and setup for {{ domain }} SSH key
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: multipart/mixed; boundary="{{ boundary }}"

--{{ boundary }}
Content-Type: text/plain; charset="utf-8"

Hello {{ username }},

Attached you will find the private SSH key and configuration artifacts for {{ domain }}.
Files included:
 - Private SSH key: {{ filename | default(username + '_private_key') }}

Credentials
Username: {{ username }}
Password: {{ password | default('N/A') }}

Quick setup instructions (Windows PowerShell):

1) Save the attached private key to your .ssh folder:
	- Linux/macOS: ~/.ssh/{{ filename | default(username + '_private_key') }}
	- Windows (PowerShell): $env:USERPROFILE\\.ssh\\{{ filename | default(username + '_private_key') }}

2) Generate the public key from the private key:

Quick setup instructions (Windows PowerShell):

1) Save the attached private key to your .ssh folder:
	- PowerShell: $env:USERPROFILE\\.ssh\\{{ filename | default(username + '_private_key') }}
	- CMD: %USERPROFILE%\\.ssh\\{{ filename | default(username + '_private_key') }}

2) Generate the public key from the private key (PowerShell):
	ssh-keygen -y -f "$env:USERPROFILE\\.ssh\\{{ filename | default(username + '_private_key') }}" > "$env:USERPROFILE\\.ssh\\{{ filename | default(username + '_public_key') }}.pub"

3) Example SSH config entry (Windows OpenSSH format, edit %USERPROFILE%\\.ssh\\config):
	Host {{ domain }} {{ ip | default('IP_ADDRESS') }}
		HostName {{ ip | default('IP_ADDRESS') }}
		Port {{ ssh_port | default(22) }}
		User {{ username }}
		IdentityFile $env:USERPROFILE\\.ssh\\{{ filename | default(username + '_private_key') }}
		IdentitiesOnly yes
Content-Transfer-Encoding: base64
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="{{ filename | default(username + '_private_key') }}"

{{ private_key_b64 }}

--{{ boundary }}
Content-Type: application/octet-stream; name="secrets.yml"
Content-Transfer-Encoding: base64
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="secrets.yml"

{{ secrets_b64 | default('') }}

--{{ boundary }}
Content-Type: application/octet-stream; name="all.yml"
Content-Transfer-Encoding: base64
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="all.yml"

{{ all_b64 | default('') }}

--{{ boundary }}--
